This paper deals with resource allocation and user association in a network consisting of drones, satellites, and terrestrial base stations. The problem involves managing resources over multiple links and optimizing the quality of service while minimizing energy consumption. This makes it likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves modeling the problem as a competitive market, which suggests that it could also belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The use of optimization techniques and iterative algorithms for finding the Walrasian equilibrium makes it likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the use of drones and satellites for backhaul connectivity suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
